attributes.Long form description: The student grabs the DSLR and inspects it to detach the lens but he has trouble so the instructor helps him. The student finally finds the release button and presses it to detach the lens. Next, the student attaches the lens back again. The instructor tells the student to detach the cover lens but the student detaches the lens hood instead so the instructor corrects him and the student put it back in place. He grabs the lens cover and finally detaches it from the DSLR. Then he attaches again the lens cover. The instructor tells the student to turn on the DSLR, so the student inspects and rotates the DSLR searching for the power button. Finally, the student localizes the power button and presses it. He waits for the DSLR to turn on. Then the student presses again the button to turn off the DSLR. The instructor tells the student to change the battery so he searches for the battery slot and inspects the DSLR. The student removes the old battery and inserts a new one. Next, the student searches for the SD card slot, and when he finds it, removes the old SD card and inserts a new one. After that, the student places the DSLR on the table and finishes the task.
